nd used its outputs as building blocks.=C2=A0
Why does Scenius emerge from catastrophe?=C2=A0
For one, catastrophe focuses energy, attention, and talent. The US Governme=
nt pulled the brightest minds in the nation together to develop new technol=
ogy to power the war effort, and those technologies, like the transistors t=
hat came out of Bell Labs, formed the foundation of Silicon Valley.=C2=A0
Second, crisis shakes and breaks and calls for new solutions. When everythi=
ng is burnt to the ground, there=E2=80=99s room for new ideas and instituti=
ons to grow. Ben Franklin=E2=80=99s Junto created the first volunteer fire =
company, public library, and philosophical society in the young United Stat=
es of America, along with the University of Pennsylvania.=C2=A0
Third, catastrophe brings people together in ways that are difficult to acc=
omplish in peacetime. In Tribe [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkctuxC=
AMRb9m2E3EI-SxYNEuqqrbdh_xcDJoEogITJR-fT2TRSVkg6-tax2szjDFdKg1bpk8w5CPFVSAf=
ZshZ0ikbJAG7xRreCdk3ROnasc62RG_DWMCWLSfVU4FyFrM7K3OPobXBKVckpvirRidpGY0lhmn=
GdNay7GVtHMoSXv66uI8BAsKHpCOGIDM6pbzul3E24V_4Nn3vdKL_o2hsnHBwk_yBq6fcQF8-zB=
d32GOYXrevsHoLXsdrl8lTJCw260YWC2lbBrRMeIVp5wx3JFxWQtW8cqAYLgpo0w2sm9p9bBRmt=
CXS02XiVdbMVvW9v70J0mFmE1MaIfy_aYXmF8CYhgwLyX4fAwQtJnBnYTyCfrFbJggQMIPcIPOi=
FdI1jR128imP4kgwlpQ0faCEXR2EafCv-kfSRGU2A], Sebastian Junger wrote: =C2=A0
Disasters, he proposed, create a =E2=80=9Ccommunity of sufferers=E2=80=9D t=
hat allows individuals to experience an immensely reassuring connection to =
others. As people come together to face an existential threat, Fritz found,=
 class differences are temporarily erased, income disparities become irrele=
vant, race is overlooked, and individuals are assessed simply by what they =
are willing to do for the group.
Even after the catastrophe ends, there seems to be an afterglow, during whi=
ch newly-formed channels of collaboration continue to bear fruit.=C2=A0
Those four factors -- human mixing, new educational models, institutions th=
at encourage risk-taking, and catastrophe -- set the stage for Scenius. The=
n the endogenous factors take over, and it=E2=80=99s up to the scene to mak=
e its impact.
Endogenous Factors
A little over a decade after Brian Eno named and defined scenius, Wired=E2=
=80=99s Kevin Kelly [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOgzAM_JrmiOI8e=
Bxy2Mv-BgqJSyNCgoKh4u83LYeVLFvWaDyecZZwzuUyW96JfdpI14Ym4XuPSISFHTuWMXgDreil=
VgPzRnnodc_CPj4L4mpDNFQOZNsxxeAshZy-DM6FZi8D0Ds5eLTPViN3wJUQ3FtlVQeaq_7WtYc=
PmBwaPLFcOSGL5kW07Q_58xC_tegdPh81Lq91W_AMSSwY48WCEVwAVDkQWkloRDOhBK85cNCtHj=
renC7rKQ3HQ_F1Fs1-TDtZt3yusWJSpimXkOYKLy-7YvwC1dFY53qkQNeIyU4R_W2W7sy-9scZE=
5aapR8t1aSkhrZVXavb4TZX01CSy26QwKqyz5WV_kX_AGDOgu4] popularized the term in=
 the tech community and put a framework around it. In a 2008 blog post, Sce=
nius, or Communal Genius [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQRk_T=
7Mbw37pgMZu5hkEolahgoOiJtx-6XUxCSEGl6uV7ziIsKV_mTAXJ-xrxOsFE-C07IEImtUAegzd=
M814oORBvpGe96kko45wBDht2g7kCOeu0B2cxpPiZoJQrshrn2Oxozx3Ttnd0sFpYKQc2ezbNbm=
Y311YfIDow8IJ8pQhkNyviWR7i-8F_2tm2LuWlFbgCgltjqEd7FQetKl8pf7l0vH9IMJxyxhqec=
SUF63g3gWBeUUaZ0mp40u7lkpriUB-SHgvvSp0KWrd1bQfJJiacUg5xae1ttQfsn0ZLOL4hNQa8=
Roh22sHf4fF2-NExLhAhN7d-tNjMCcW0lk-t9HCHbXakoOI5CEYa2ac2Ff-hf6LjiPo], Kelly=
 looked at some historical examples and came up with four factors that nurt=
ure scenius once it takes root:=C2=A0
Mutual appreciation: Risky moves are applauded by the group, subtlety is ap=
preciated, and friendly competition goads the shy. Scenius can be thought o=
f as the best of peer pressure.
Rapid exchange of tools and techniques: As soon as something is invented, i=
t is flaunted and then shared. Ideas flow quickly because they are flowing =
inside a common language and sensibility.
Network effects of success: When a record is broken, a hit happens, or brea=
kthrough erupts, the success is claimed by the entire scene. This empowers =
the scene to further success.
Local tolerance for the novelties: The local =E2=80=9Coutside=E2=80=9D does=
 not push back too hard against the transgressions of the scene. The renega=
des and mavericks are protected by this buffer zone.
Kelly=E2=80=99s four factors are present in any scenius, from the purely ar=
tistic to something as local and specific as Yosemite Park=E2=80=99s Camp 4=
=2E In Conjuring Scenius [https://email.m=
g2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMuOwyAMRb-m7C=
biEWhYsJjN_Abi4aZME4h4NMrfD2kWI1m2ZMv36h5nKswpH2pLpaKz6XpsoCLsZYFaIaNWIOvgF=
RF0YnyUyKvRk4lPKBT9yACrCYuquQHaml2CMzWk-PnAmHL0VE4AUJAP_vAUmCfgnHWMTUwyZq2g=
l69pPkB0oOAN-UgR0KKetW7lxr5v9KfXvu_DZtzrWAeX1r6wS5r7cCn-thzi_FUcxNAKCopiSki=
3J5SPjAx0sMCI55hgwgWXdzy8XeI2ynYb8TrToTRbahc_pVFWMVWbTs1-fj3NCsvn0BPqPtcWQz=
00RGMX8Ff4ejH84NAzRMidrdemdnKMEyHGu-BCXmE7nZFhdpeMoO7sU_-K_6Z_hGKJ8Q], I ad=
ded four ingredients that seem to be present in all of the examples of the =
great Scenia that had a lasting impact on the world. One was emergence from=
 catastrophe, described above, and the remaining three are endogenous facto=
rs that can be used to strengthen the Scenius:=C2=A0
Competition: Healthy competition sharpens the blades of new ideas within th=
e safety of the scene, and pushes participants to achieve bigger and better=
 things. The Ancient Greek philosophical schools competed in a =E2=80=9Cmar=
ketplace of ideas,=E2=80=9D and competition between Michaelangelo and Leona=
rdo (the artists, not the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles) raised the status o=
f art in culture, and pushed both men to advance the craft.=C2=A0
Place-Based Ritual: A scene needs a setting. The Junto met in a bar, The In=
klings in The Eagle and Child Pub, Motown=E2=80=99s artists in Detroit hous=
es, and Renaissance artists in le botteghe. Informal meeting places enable =
all four of Kelly=E2=80=99s ingredients.=C2=A0=C2=A0
Diversity of Thought and Experience: New ideas form at the intersections of=
 existing ones, and the mashup of people from diverse backgrounds, with div=
erse thoughts and experiences, provides fodder for the new. This is both an=
 exogenous factor -- diverse people need to be in a certain place at a cert=
ain time for their ideas to mix -- and an endogenous one -- the scene needs=
 to be welcoming to new people, ideas, and perspectives.=C2=A0
Those eleven factors -- four exogenous and seven endogenous -- can turn gro=
ups of individuals into a Scenius, a community that accomplishes much more,=
 across a range of disciplines, than would otherwise be expected from a gro=
up of people with the same talents.=C2=A0
There have certainly been groupings of people as intelligent as those alive=
 in Ancient Greece or Florence during the Renaissance who lived in the same=
 place around the same time; without the right underlying conditions, howev=
er, they weren=E2=80=99t able to combine their talents in any way meaningfu=
l enough that we remember and build upon their contributions today.=C2=A0
When they are in place, though, magic happens. And they=E2=80=99re in place=
 right now.
To see how that framework fits the WAGMI Scenius and where this is all head=
